import React, { useState } from 'react'; const FilterPanel = ({ onFilterChange }) => { const [filters, setFilters] = useState({ make: '', model: '', fuelType: '', transmission: '', year: '' }); const handleChange = (e) => { const { name, value } = e.target; setFilters({ ...filters, [name]: value }); }; const handleSubmit = (e) => { e.preventDefault(); onFilterChange(filters); }; return (
); }; export default FilterPanel;
